Apollo Investment Corporation (AINV) Upgraded to Hold by Zacks Investment Research

					Posted by Mitch Edgeman on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 




Zacks Investment Research upgraded shares of Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV) from a sell rating to a hold rating in a research note issued to investors on Wednesday. 
According to Zacks, “Apollo Investment Corporation is a closed-end investment company that has elected to be treated as a business development company under the Investment Company Act of 1940. The Company’s investment portfolio will be principally in middle-market private companies.   “


 Get Apollo Investment Corporation alerts:



A number of other analysts have also recently commented on the company. BMO Capital Markets  reaffirmed a hold rating and set a $6.00 price target on shares of Apollo Investment Corporation in a research report on Thursday, May 18th. Jefferies Group LLC  reaffirmed a buy rating and set a $7.00 price target on shares of Apollo Investment Corporation in a research report on Friday, July 14th. Keefe, Bruyette & Woods  set a $7.00 price target on Apollo Investment Corporation and gave the stock a hold rating in a research report on Wednesday, May 31st. Finally, National Securities  reaffirmed a neutral rating and set a $6.00 price target on shares of Apollo Investment Corporation in a research report on Thursday, May 18th. Five research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and one  has given a buy rating to the company’s stock. Apollo Investment Corporation currently has an average rating of Hold and a consensus target price of $6.40.




Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV) traded up 0.31% on Wednesday, reaching $6.39. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 174,126 shares. Apollo Investment Corporation has a 1-year low of $5.42 and a 1-year high of $6.82. The firm’s 50 day moving average price is $6.38 and its 200-day moving average price is $6.34. 
Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, May 18th. The asset manager reported $0.17 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.16 by $0.01. Apollo Investment Corporation had a return on equity of 9.81% and a net margin of 6.56%. The firm had revenue of $66.30 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $68.89 million. During the same period in the previous year, the business earned $0.20 EPS. The firm’s revenue for the quarter was down 22.3% on a year-over-year basis.  Analysts predict that  Apollo Investment Corporation will post $0.64 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Apollo Investment Corporation (AINV) Upgraded to Hold by Zacks Investment Research” was first  reported by Markets Daily and is the sole property of of Markets Daily. If you are accessing this news story on another site, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of US and international trademark and copyright laws. The original version of this news story can be viewed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/20/apollo-investment-corporation-ainv-upgraded-to-hold-by-zacks-investment-research.html. 
The business also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Thursday, July 6th. Stockholders of record on Wednesday, June 21st were issued a $0.15 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Monday, June 19th. This represents a $0.60 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 9.42%. Apollo Investment Corporation’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 750.00%. 
Institutional investors have recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Graybill Bartz & Assoc Ltd. boosted its position in  Apollo Investment Corporation by 0.4% in the first quarter. Graybill Bartz & Assoc Ltd. now owns 372,693 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $2,445,000 after buying an additional 1,464 shares during the last quarter.  Creative Planning boosted its position in  Apollo Investment Corporation by 8.5% in the first quarter. Creative Planning now owns 73,730 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $484,000 after buying an additional 5,759 shares during the last quarter.  Highbridge Capital Management LLC acquired a new position in  Apollo Investment Corporation during the fourth quarter worth $1,436,000.  Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company LTD boosted its position in  Apollo Investment Corporation by 122.1% in the first quarter. Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company LTD now owns 816,242 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $5,354,000 after buying an additional 448,680 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Advisors Asset Management Inc. boosted its position in  Apollo Investment Corporation by 35.9% in the first quarter. Advisors Asset Management Inc. now owns 381,380 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $2,502,000 after buying an additional 100,663 shares during the last quarter. 46.20% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 
About Apollo Investment Corporation
Apollo Investment Corporation is a closed-end, externally managed, non-diversified management investment company. The Company’s investment objective is to generate current income and capital appreciation. It invests primarily in various forms of debt investments, including secured and unsecured debt, loan investments and/or equity in private middle-market companies.
