Stock News






Amica Mutual Insurance Company Decreased United Technologies (UTX) Position; Apollo Investment (AINV)’s Sentiment Is 1.94


					
						July 19, 2017 - By Ellis Scott

Apollo Investment Corporation is a closed-end, externally managed, non-diversified management investment company. The company has market cap of $1.41 billion. The Company’s investment objective is to generate current income and capital appreciation. It has a 74.65 P/E ratio. It invests primarily in various forms of debt investments, including secured and unsecured debt, loan investments and/or equity in private middle-market companies.







Amica Mutual Insurance Company decreased United Technologies Corp (UTX) stake by 26.72% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Amica Mutual Insurance Company sold 20,831 shares as United Technologies Corp (UTX)’s stock rose 8.03%. The Amica Mutual Insurance Company holds 57,142 shares with $6.26M value, down from 77,973 last quarter. United Technologies Corp now has $98.02B valuation. The stock decreased 0.39% or $0.48 during the last trading session, reaching $122.63. About 100 shares traded. United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) has risen 22.99% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 6.29% the S&P500.
Analysts await Apollo Investment Corp. (NASDAQ:AINV) to report earnings on August, 4 before the open. They expect $0.15 earnings per share, down 6.25% or $0.01 from last year’s $0.16 per share. AINV’s profit will be $33.20M for 10.62 P/E if the $0.15 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.17 actual earnings per share reported by Apollo Investment Corp. for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -11.76% negative EPS growth. 
It closed at $6.37 lastly. It is down 17.01% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 0.31% the S&P500.
Muzinich & Co. Inc. holds 4.85% of its portfolio in Apollo Investment Corp. for 6.28 million shares. Greenwich Investment Management Inc. owns 586,700 shares or 3.51% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Raiff Partners Inc has 3.37% invested in the company for 235,000 shares. The Ohio-based Camelot Portfolios Llc has invested 2.98% in the stock. Tegean Capital Management Llc, a New York-based fund reported 500,000 shares.
Since February 6, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 10 sales for $11.15 million activity. $322,969 worth of stock was sold by Bailey Robert J. on Wednesday, May 3. Gill Charles D had sold 16,329 shares worth $1.81M. HAYES GREGORY also sold $1.93 million worth of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) shares. 300 United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) shares with value of $33,396 were sold by MCDONOUGH ROBERT J. Dumais Michael R had sold 2,541 shares worth $284,906. Amato Elizabeth B sold $335,057 worth of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) on Thursday, February 16. Gitlin David L. also sold $1.00 million worth of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) shares.
Amica Mutual Insurance Company increased Marathon Petroleum Corp (NYSE:MPC) stake by 6,940 shares to 46,037 valued at $2.32 million in 2016Q4. It also upped Conocophillips (NYSE:COP) stake by 18,303 shares and now owns 114,487 shares. New Germany Fund Inc (GF) was raised too. 
Among 21 analysts covering United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX), 7 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 14 Hold. Therefore 33% are positive. United Technologies Corporation had 53 analyst reports since July 21, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) earned “Neutral” rating by Robert W. Baird on Thursday, October 6. The stock of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) earned “Buy” rating by S&P Research on Tuesday, July 21. The rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets on Thursday, April 27 with “Sector Perform”. The stock of United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) has “Hold” rating given on Tuesday, August 25 by Deutsche Bank. Argus Research maintained United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) rating on Wednesday, July 22. Argus Research has “Buy” rating and $125 target. As per Friday, June 2, the company rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets. UBS maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Monday, September 19 report. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Friday, April 28 by Jefferies. The firm has “Hold” rating by Stifel Nicolaus given on Friday, January 27. On Thursday, September 10 the stock rating was maintained by Citigroup with “Buy”.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.06, from 1.06 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 70 investors sold UTX shares while 516 reduced holdings. 100 funds opened positions while 484 raised stakes. 623.51 million shares or 1.02% less from 629.95 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Utd Finance Advisers Limited Liability Com owns 210,385 shares. Founders Mngmt Limited Liability Co, Connecticut-based fund reported 68,345 shares. White Pine Company has 2.42% invested in United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX). Ny State Teachers Retirement invested 0.38% of its portfolio in United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX). Eads & Heald Investment Counsel holds 1.34% of its portfolio in United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) for 17,992 shares. Tru Department Mb Bank & Trust N A invested in 2,004 shares or 0.02% of the stock. Huntington State Bank reported 250,982 shares. Lpl Financial Ltd Company holds 0.02% or 29,441 shares in its portfolio. Pinnacle Fincl Prtn has invested 0.82% in United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX). Hartford Financial Mngmt holds 39,848 shares or 2.59% of its portfolio. Bridgeway Capital holds 142,785 shares. Ashfield Cap Partners Ltd Limited Liability Company reported 17,935 shares or 0.19% of all its holdings. Wexford Capital Lp accumulated 0.12% or 10,714 shares. Bellecapital International holds 0.59% or 6,072 shares in its portfolio. Kelly Lawrence W Associate Ca invested in 2,187 shares.
Analysts await United Technologies Corporation (NYSE:UTX) to report earnings on July, 25 before the open. They expect $1.77 earnings per share, down 2.75% or $0.05 from last year’s $1.82 per share. UTX’s profit will be $1.41 billion for 17.32 P/E if the $1.77 EPS becomes a reality. After $1.48 actual earnings per share reported by United Technologies Corporation for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 19.59% EPS growth. 








By Ellis Scott
