In Volatile Markets Do Analysts Think You Should Buy Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV)?


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Friday, 21 Jul 2017 05:49 AM  / 0 Comments




Following U.S. election volatility some analysts have updated their recommended target prices on shares of Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV).  	 According to the most recently released broker notes, 1 analyst has a rating of “strong buy” on the stock, 2 analysts “buy”, 9 analysts “neutral”, 1 analysts “sell” and 0 analysts “strong sell”. 	  



Latest Recommended Buy/Sell Side Ratings:
07/08/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at Bank of America Merrill Lynch. 
06/13/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at UBS.  They now have a USD 6.5 price target on the stock.
05/20/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at BB&T Capital Markets. 
05/20/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at Keefe, Bruyette & Woods.  They now have a USD 5.75 price target on the stock.
05/20/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Jefferies.  They now have a USD 7 price target on the stock.
02/11/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at JMP Securities. 
02/10/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at SunTrust.  They now have a USD 7 price target on the stock.
02/10/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Maxim Group.  They now have a USD 7.5 price target on the stock.
02/10/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at BMO Capital Markets.  They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
02/10/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays.  They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
02/10/2016 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at Citigroup. 
11/06/2015 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at JP Morgan.  They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
11/06/2015 – Apollo Investment Corporation had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at RBC Capital.  They now have a USD 8 price target on the stock.
09/30/2015 – D.A. Davidson began new coverage on Apollo Investment Corporation giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
09/01/2015 – Apollo Investment Corporation was downgraded to “” by analysts at Cantor Fitzgerald.  They now have a USD 7 price target on the stock.
The share price of Apollo Investment Corporation (NASDAQ:AINV) was down -0.31% during the last trading session, with a day high of 6.39. 415307 shares were traded on Apollo Investment Corporation’s last session. 
The stock’s 50 day moving average is 6.38 and its 200 day moving average is 6.34. Apollo Investment Corporation has a 52-week low of 5.42 and a 52-week high of 6.82.



Apollo Investment Corporation is a closed-end, externally managed, non-diversified management investment company. The Company’s investment objective is to generate current income and capital appreciation. It invests primarily in various forms of debt investments, including secured and unsecured debt, loan investments and/or equity in private middle-market companies. It may also invest in the securities of public companies and in structured products and other investments, such as collateralized loan obligations (CLOs) and credit-linked notes (CLNs). Its portfolio also includes equity interests, such as common stock, preferred stock, warrants or options. It invests in investments in the United States secured and unsecured loans, other debt securities and equity, and may also invests a portion of the portfolio in other investment opportunities, including foreign securities and structured products. Apollo Investment Management, L.P. is the investment advisor of the Company.


